:2,"refillPrice":496.00000000000000000,"remainderConsCost":0.00000000000000000,"totalCost":163054.00000000000000000},{"averageConsumptionCost":471.82851867000000000,"bunkerGradeName":"LSGO","consCost":51476.49138798000000000,"consTotal":109.10000000000000000,"displayOrder":6,"refillPrice":580.00000000000000000,"remainderConsCost":0.00000000000000000,"totalCost":51476.49138798000000000}],"emissionsDetails":{"voyageCIIBand":null,"voyageCO2":null,"voyageEEOI":null,"voyageAER":null,"voyageSOxMt":null,"voyageSOx":null,"voyageNOxMt":null,"voyageNOx":null,"euEtsDetails":null,"legEmissionsDetails":[]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2021-09-16T16:03:33.873","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Operator comments: Thankfully this voyage didn\u2019t come with any hiccups, and we were able to drastically improve the TCE.  We collected $51k in demurrage basis 2.84 days x 18k/pd and overall expenses decreased by $18k.  Bunker consumption decreased by $3k considering passage outside of ECA on laden passage.  However, this added .25 days which essentially cancelled out the savings.  While we did restock TC chems in Balboa, cleaning wasn\u2019t necessary which saved us approx. $10k.  Overall port costs were $8k less than anticipated, but it\u2019s important to note when calling the Exxon terminal in Beaumont; tug costs are about $9k more than we typically see.  This is due to terminal location being further up river.  While TCE increased by $2,400, the additional days still resulted in our PnL remaining roughly the same.\n\t\n\tImprovements: nil\n\t\nFixture comments: Wisby Pacific came open Peru end of July where we couldn\u2019t find a west coast cargo that made sense hence Ballasting her into the usg. We managed to get her fixed to Exxon loading perfect on our dates 16th from Beaumont to Halifax Canada at 120 ws which Is (2kpd) open Halifax. However to put it in perspective, the previous voyage was 6,400pd or a loss of (400k) including the ballast back to Crist\u00F3bal which from that Cristobal position makes this current voyage about 9kpd open Canada. Furthermore those returns would be equivalent to about 120-125ws usg-braz knowing market dropped to 110ws usg brazil within the hour after going on subs. In short with everything considered, would say this is a decent voyage. Wisby Pacific will open Eccan end of August, perhaps in time for a Quebec cargo. \n\t\n\nFIXTURE NOTE\nVessel\tWisby Pacific\nVoy#\t2105\nFix#\tXOM 16th usg-eccan\nC/P Date\tAug 13, 2021\nCharterer\tExxon\nBroker\tSouthport Ma\nStart\tCallao\nLoad\tBeaumont\nDischarge\tHalifax\nCargo\t38,000 mt CPP\nLay/Can\tAug 16-18, 2021 (00:00-16:00)\nRate\tWS 120\nComm\tCharterer: 2.5%, Broker: 1.25%, Agent: 2%\nTCE\nPNL\t-$1,815.74 for 27.4 days\n($481,143) bss Ballast from Peru\nDemurrage\t$18,000.00"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-09-07T12:16:28.35","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Panama Canal port costs accounted for in DA-desk under 2104 since port call was made during an unfixed leg"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}